This paper discusses sustainable cloud computing, which involves the intersection of computer science, software engineering, electrical engineering, and systems engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), which focuses on cloud computing and data centers. The paper also discusses application design and metrics, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses energy management and renewable energy, which are related to electrical engineering (cs.CE) and systems engineering (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses thermal-aware scheduling and cooling management, which are related to energy technology (cs.ET).
